<TEXT>
a company which operates adult bookstores 
across the street from fbi headquarters pleaded guilty monday to 
federal racketeering charges ending a twoyear investigation the 
justice department said 
fbi agents entered the stores and found videotapes with titles 
such as tracis big trick his to command and bound and 
punished according to court documents 
the plea agreement was outlined in us district court 
the agreement provides that the two stores directly across the 
street from the j edgar hoover building will be closed immediately 
while two others located just down the street will be shut down 
later 
the case is the first obscenity prosecution in the federal court 
in the district in 26 years and is only the second time the federal 
racketeering law was used in an obscenity case since congress placed 
obscenity violations under that law in 1984 according to assistant 
attorney general sg dennis jr 
automatic enterprises inc the owner of the bookstores was 
fined 150000 as part of the settlement 
