<TEXT>
with only 357 miles left the leaders in 
the iditarod trail sled dog race turned toward alaskas windblown 
coast sunday 
threetime iditarod champion susan butcher left this yukon river 
village at 655 pm ast with veteran musher martin buser one 
minute behind her 
joe runyan driving 17 dogs had led the pack of five leaders 
into kaltag earlier in the day buser arrived about an hour later 
crouching on the back of his sled brushing his teeth 
he was followed into the village seven minutes later by butcher 
who drove her team up the yukon river loudly singing a pop tune 
from kaltag the mushers race toward the coastal village of 
unalakleet 93 miles away and the longest stretch between 
checkpoints in the race from there they sprint toward the 250000 
jackpoint waiting at the finish line on nomes historic front street 
the musher who finishes first wins 50000 the rest is shared 
among the next 19 finishers 
the leaders butcher buser runyan deedee jonrowe and 
fourtime champion rick swenson have been out front of the pack 
since they left the gold mining ghost town of iditarod the halfway 
point 558 miles into the race 
fortyone mushers remain in the 1168mile contest the lowest 
number since 1985 eight have scratched since the race started march 
3 in anchorage 
