<TEXT>
eastern airlines renewed flights to seven latin 
american cities sunday and continued to lure bargain hunters to its 
northeast shuttle in an effort to rebuild despite a weekold strike 
however the airlines lure of 12 fares on the shuttle may have 
worked too well several hundred wouldbe shuttle passengers in 
boston new york and washington were told theyd have to wait for 
monday morning flights because all evening flights were booked solid 
eastern ballyhooed the reopening of its latin american routes as 
a new start for the airline which filed for bankruptcy protection 
last week blaming its pilots for honoring machinists picket lines 
and plunging the carrier into a cash crisis 
service to three more south american cities two domestic routes 
and montreal will begin later in the week the airline said 
what were really saying is it is the start of a new smaller 
restructured and viable eastern airlines said eastern spokesman 
robin matell 
eastern lured customers on its 62 bostonnew york and new 
yorkwashington shuttle flights with the 12 weekend fares down 
from 69 weekday fares begining monday will be 49 one way down 
from the usual 99 
airline officials said 31500 people crossed picket lines over 
the weekend to take the cutrate flights others tried to get aboard 
the flights and failed 
at logan international airport in boston stranded passengers 
were told to show up at the eastern terminal at 530 am monday 
when the first shuttle was slated to leave for new york 
officials at washington national airport said over 100 people who 
were unable to get onto flights would have to spend the night at the 
airport or make other travel arrangements 
in new york an undetermined number of people were stranded at 
laguardia airport 
its a bummer said terianne tapia who was up from new york 
to visit her boyfriend in boston i have to be at work at 9 am 
eastern officials said those passengers should have gotten to the 
airport sooner 
those people were not stranded we advertised the flights were 
on a firstcome firstserve basis matell said im sorry they 
have to wait for the next flight but they should have gotten there 
earlier 
asked if eastern would pay for hotel accomodations matell said 
absolutely not 
however matell later said the passengers who missed flights 
would be allowed to fly free during offpeak hours and for the same 
12 rate during peak hours if they had purchased roundtrip 
tickets over the weekend 
eastern just nine days earlier the nations seventhlargest 
carrier with 1040 daily flights planned to put 75 planes into the 
air sunday the first of the renewed latin american routes took off 
just before 4 pm for quito ecuador eastern spokeswoman virginia 
sanchez said 
matell said the shuttle and international routes were considered 
the best place to deploy easterns limited resources and generate 
revenue a 365 million sale of the shuttle to new york developer 
donald trump is pending and easterns international routes are 
among its most marketable assets 
meanwhile secretary of transportation samuel skinner said on 
cbs face the nation that the bush administration considers the 
labor dispute none of our business and has no plans to 
intervene we are not in the business of running eastern airlines 
or negotiating the contract for labor skinner said 
eastern hopes to be up to 140 flights a day by weeks end matell 
said the highest number of flights in one day since the strike 
began march 4 has been 93 
during the first week of the strike eastern maintained one 
thriceweekly flight from miami to buenos aires argentina and 
santiago chile as well as its east coast shuttle service 
easterns unions have accused frank lorenzo chairman of eastern 
parent texas air corp of trying to cannibalize the airline pilots 
and flight attendants unions have honored machinists picket lines 
which went up when the 8500member union refused to grant 125 
million in concessions to the moneylosing airline 
today eastern is up and flying company president phil bakes 
said sunday in a statement with this we begin building the great 
airline weve always known eastern could and should be 
bakes was a vice president at continental airlines in 1983 when 
lorenzo filed for chapter 11 bankruptcy protection as eastern did 
on thursday in new york 
former eastern chairman frank borman said sunday on abcs this 
week with david brinkley that he knew of no one in the management 
or on the board of texas air who wanted bankruptcy 
continental gradually rebuilt its schedule while in bankruptcy 
reorganization but eastern unions say management wont be helped as 
it was at continental by union workers crossing picket lines 
eastern estimated sunday that out of 3600 regular pilots it had 
200 flying 
the air line pilots association said the latin american routes 
are more complicated than the bostonnew yorkwashington shuttle 
which had provided nearly all of easterns strike service and it 
doubted the company had enough experienced pilots to keep flying 
them 
alpa also said the companys few pilots will be grounded by 
federal aviation administration limits on flying time such as 30 
hours within seven days matell said eastern has had no significant 
increase in delays 
matell said no decision had been made yet on when to bring in 
noncontract workers to replace strikers the company has 1500 
employees working having laid off 9500 nonunion workers last week 
in atlanta about 2000 striking workers and their families 
joined for a pep rally near the airport lorenzo was the main target 
of slogans painted and pasted on shirts cars kites and even a dog 
matell said eastern flew 10200 passengers saturday approaching 
capacity and had long lines again sunday 
lawyers for the machinists plan to go to court this week seeking 
an estimated 75 million in back wages frozen when the company 
filed bankruptcy on payday for most machinists workers the pilots 
next paycheck was due march 15 
the only good thing about bankruptcy is that it hinders 
lorenzos ability to slice this thing up like a piece of salami 
said rick chapman secretarytreasurer of the alpa local 
departures scheduled from miami starting sunday were bogota 
colombia guatemala city lima peru panama city panama quito 
ecuador guayaquil ecuador and san jose costa rica thriceweekly 
flights were planned to start later in the week for asuncion 
paraguay cali colombia and la paz bolivia 
our loads are looking good said eastern spokeswoman virginia 
sanchez noting heavy passenger turnout for flights to panama city 
and lima 
the company also intends to resume thricedaily flights between 
miami and puerto rico on monday along with service to montreal then 
add direct flights later this week between washington and boston 
