on april 16 1968 army capt thomas jay 
hayes iv was killed in vietnam after dragging two wounded comrades 
to safety as enemy forces overwhelmed his platoon 
on sunday hayes became the latest fallen hero to have a building 
on the west point campus renamed in his honor 
as his classmates from the west point class of 66 gathered for 
