the sound it was the most dramatic thing that ever happened to me 
it is the happiest circumstance of my life that changing the world 
is what made me successful 
it was also what had drawn him to journalism in the first place 
at columbia university school of journalism where wabc sent him for 
a crash course he came to regard reporting as a vehicle for change 
among his professors was fred friendly he impressed me with 
the nobility the morality says geraldo journalism was bigger 
than clark kent big it was paul revere big 
he never wanted to be tom brokaw he wanted to bring grim 
reality not pinstriped sensibility to the small screen he became 
the ghettocrimepunishment reporter i was always 
staggeringly selfconfident in street situations he says with his 
usual modesty 
the swagger survives along with arrogance passion and pride 
my fatal flaw he concedes 
it was that pride that cost him his network job in 1985 roone 
arledge pulled a 2020 segment on marilyn monroes relationship 
with the kennedys and geraldo threw a tantrum a less impulsive man 
might have stopped to consider that he had not yet signed his new 
contract before publicly mouthing off at the boss 
i died of massive mostly selfinflicted wounds he wrote in 
the april 1986 issue of esquire 
his obituary was premature he soon attempted a comeback as a 
freelancer with the mystery of al capones vault 
the gangsters vault opened with much fanfare on live 
television came up empty mortified geraldo went into hiding 
setting off on what was to be an epic voyage aboard his 44foot 
sloop the new wave 
he came ashore in a hurry after learning that al capones 
vault was the highestrated nationally syndicated show of all time 
five specials and one talk show later he is philosophical about 
the career turn that has made him more of an outsider than ever he 
isnt exactly unhappy but neither is he free of regret 
ideally i want to be sorting through the ashes trying to find 
truth id like to be challenging institutional politics or 
reporting on the budget deficit or the middle east 
but a lot of what im doing is really righteous stuff they 
wont remember me for the chippendales or prostitution they are 
going to remember me for the stories that made a difference 
he remains unrepentant about his most recent thrashing by the 
