<TEXT>
general mills inc monday said its 
thirdquarter income rose 153 percent and pershare profit grew to 
a record amount 
the company reported aftertax earnings of 823 million for the 
quarter ended feb 26 up from 714 million a year earlier 
on a pershare basis earnings hit a record 1 compared with 83 
cents a share during the same period a year earlier the record 
coincided with a decline in the number of outstanding shares from 
865 million a year ago to 822 million shares chairman bruce 
atwater said 
sales in the quarter grew 17 percent to 145 billion from 124 
billion the year before 
atwater said the increases in the 13week period ended feb 26 
reflect strengths in big g cereals and red lobster and the olive 
garden restaurants he said cereals have experienced a 19 percent 
unit volume gain and 105 new restaurants have opened in the past 12 
months 
restaurants led the companys third quarter operating performance 
with gains in sales and operating profits of 33 percent and 63 
percent respectively atwater said 
established red lobster restaurants showed average unit sales 
gains of 14 percent in the previous quarter 27 seafood broiler 
units in southern california were converted to red lobster 
restaurants the conversions cost about 200000 a restaurant 
