changes to vehicles which fail to meet emission standards 
cars made for sale in canada and california arent subject to the 
recall ford said 
tracers sold in the united states and canada were recalled to 
check for a worn spark plug wire which can cause poor starting 
engine misfiring substandard performance and poor fuel economy 
worn wires will be replaced 
about 28200 of the tracers also will be checked for bumper 
covers which have faded from exposure to ultraviolet light faded 
covers will be replaced with covers with light stabilizers 
vehicles owners in each of the recalls will be notified by mail 
and repairs will be performed at no cost 
