the weekend after friday prices will return to the normal 69 on 
weekends and 99 on weekdays and sunday evening 
the cutrate weekend fare in effect friday through sunday was 
intended to show the airline is still in business despite the 10day 
old walkout by eastern machinists and the sympathy of most pilots 
while it drew 31500 passengers many were as surprised as eastern 
when it ran out of seats to take the bargain hunters home 
an estimated 550 people were unexpectedly grounded sunday in the 
three cities linked by the shuttle 
created by eastern in 1961 the shuttle normally offers hourly 
service between boston new york and washington pan am corp which 
runs a rival shuttle between the three cities did not match 
easterns special fare 
seats cant be reserved on either the eastern or pan am shuttle 
but they are normally guaranteed even if it means wheeling out 
another plane 
but with last weekends unusual deal eastern warned in advance 
that there would be no backup flights although the crush forced the 
airline to bring out its biggest jets and five backup flights 
anyone unable to return on the weekend was allowed to fly home free 
through wednesday as long as they took an eastern flight between 10 
am and 3 pm est 
the gimmick went down well with some industry observers 
they wanted to provoke a public reaction and they did they 
just didnt think deeply about it said mark daugherty airline 
analyst with dean witter reynolds inc in new york 
buyer beware whenever there is a good deal the buyer has to 
assume a certain amount of risk he said 
